Defendant Jesse J Bullis in court, in custody by video from Prairie du Chien, with attorney Eric Daniel Lowenberg.    District Attorney's Office Tim Suha appeared for the State of Wisconsin. State moves to strike the repeater allegations.  Defendant enters a guilty plea as to counts 3 and 9. Defendant enters a guilty plea as to count 10. Court imposed the following sentence: 

  The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

IMPOSED SENTENCE of: Count 9

10 YEARS IMPRISONMENT 
  -  5 YEAR(S) OF INITIAL CONFINEMENT
  -  5 YEAR(S) OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION;
Sentence to run consecutive

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia.
*No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
*Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed.
*Inform Agent of all prescriptions
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
*Not to possess any weapons 
*No contact with the victims or their residence unless they wish to have contact and no contact with the co-actors
*DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done.

RESTITUTION:  $27,273.14 jointly and severally  (to be paid as a condition of extended supervision - restitution to be paid before costs or fines);
COURT COSTS:  $268.00  (to be paid as a condition of extended supervision);
DNA SURCHARGE:  $250.00  (to be paid as a condition of extended supervision);

Defendant is not eligible for Challenge Incarceration Program.
Defendant is eligible for Substance Abuse Program.

Felony warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.

Defendant to have a restitution hearing as to his ability to pay the restitution. 



